  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You are about to cast a spell that has a range and targets one creature.</p><hr /><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">You ensure even the farthest admirer of your work can appreciate it with the aid of a catalyst. Your catalyzed spell’s range increases by 30 feet. As normal for increasing spell ranges, if the spell has a range of touch, you extend its range to 30 feet.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">You can instead choose to use this feat without using an ephemeral catalyst. If you do, this action loses the Catalyze trait but requires you to spend an action, and your next action must be to Cast a Spell that meets the trigger’s requirements, as normal for Spellshapes.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\"><strong>Enhanced Catalyst</strong> You spend your catalyst and take the time to empower your technique. You add 1 to this action’s catalyze trait and you extend the spell’s range by 60 feet instead.</span></p>"
